Jama Masjid in Agra is opposite the Agra fort and overlooking the Agra Fort Railway Station. The Jama Masjid is also popularly known as the Jami Masjid or "Friday Mosque". It is one of the largest mosques in India.

Jama Masjid at Agra also known as 'Friday Mosque' is a seventeenth-century structure and is one of the largest mosques built by the Mughals in India. Constructed under the reign of Shah Jahan in 1648, Jama Masjid is dedicated to his favourite daughter Jahan Ara Begum. This splendid monument is visible from the Agra Fort with the Agra Fort Railway station right between the two structures. Jama Masjid has huge significance in the Indian history and culture and has been intricately designed with multi coloured marbles and sandstone.

Holy place birth place of lord Krishna. Amazing experience with great atmosphere because there is a magic in enchanting of people Hare Rama Hare Krishna. Tourist attraction of devotees. Devotees from other countries visits most of the time. it was a incredible experience there that there is no permission to stay inside of the prison of lord Krishna but the female foreigner(devotee) were feeding her child milk. that emotion of mother and child was great. Must visit this place in a life. Another one important thing is that security has high level. You cannot take a single pin inside. Mobile phones, Cameras and other equipment cannot take inside. Stay aware while buying merchandise inside the temple because they will tell you high price you must have to bargain while purchasing any thing. Overall feel the peaceful breath inside the temple. Hare Krishna
